---
title: Roasted Chicken Breast and Pan-Fried Halloumi with Caramelised Red Onion and Lentils
description: The UK now eats more halloumi than anywhere else in the world, apart from Cyprus where it's made. We can see why! Everyone loves this 'squeaky cheese' with its delicious salty taste and firm texture. It's particularly good in today's recipe, paired with nutty lentils and sweet balsamic onions.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-chicken-breast-and-pan-fried-halloumi-c69fcc68-c84d24ff.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/roasted-chicken-breast-and-pan-fried-halloumi-5fd9e871ad0f8004482f746c-a93622f2.pdf
author: Mimi Morley
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Middle Eastern
nutrition:
  calories: 823 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 39 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 78 g
  sodium: 4.5 g
  serving size: 609
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/roasted-chicken-breast-and-pan-fried-halloumi-5fd9e871ad0f8004482f746c
time required: 35 minutes
---

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Pop the tomatoes on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt and @pepper. Toss to coat.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the @halloumi{250} into three slices per person. Place the halloumi slices in a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. While the pan gets hot, season the @chicken breasts{2} with @salt and @pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Once hot, lay in the chicken and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes} each side. Once browned, pop the chicken on a baking tray and roast in your #oven{} on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

Once the chicken is in the oven, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the red onion. Season with salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until really soft, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, pop a #lid{} on and turn the heat down to low. Cook until caramelised, stirring occasionally, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{50%ml} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the lentils. Bring to the boil and cook the lentils until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

While everything cooks, bake the tomatoes in your oven until the tomatoes softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once cooked remove from the oven and set aside.

Once the lentils are piping hot, add in the @baby spinach{100} a handful at a time and cook until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}. When wilted, pop a lid on and remove from the heat. Set aside.

While the spinach wilts, put a frying pan on medium heat and add a drizzle of oil. Once the oil is hot, lay in the halloumi slices. Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, then remove the pan from the heat.

Thinly slice the chicken. Stir the tomatoes into the lentils, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve the lentils in #bowls{} with the halloumi slices, chicken and @croutons{1} on top. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 2: If you've added chicken breast to your meal then before you do the step above, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium high heat. While the pan gets hot, season the chicken with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Once hot, lay in the chicken and cook until browned, 4-5 mins each side. Once browned, pop the chicken on a baking tray and roast in your oven on the top shelf until cooked through, 12-15 mins. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. When cooked, remove from your oven, cover with foil and allow to rest for a couple of mins. Once the chicken is in the oven, continue with the step as instructed (using the same pan).

> Mod Step 6: If you've added chicken breast to your meal, once the chicken has rested, thinly slice. Serve on top of the lentils in along with the croutons and halloumi.